6072	   ZopfliCleanHash).  The preconditions below are the minimal caller-visible
6073	   requirements: options/in/splitpoints/npoints are valid distinct objects and the
6074	   window is non-empty (inend > instart, as ZopfliInitBlockState requires
6075	   blockend > blockstart).
6076	
6077	   The two output pointers are the only caller-visible writes (everything else --
6078	   the store, the block state with its LMC, the hash, and lz77splitpoints -- is a
6079	   stack/heap local allocated and freed within the body), so the assigns clause is
6080	   exactly { *npoints, *splitpoints } and the postcondition records the documented
6081	   post-state *npoints == 0 (the body sets *npoints = 0 and, with the tiny-file
